          "source_document_id": "src-bmo-html-49c8d8984f930b1c",
          "source_snapshot_id": "snap-7feab1d60acd1387",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-a6af3718bb730576",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "What is the best chequing account in Canada?\nThere isn\u2019t one \u201cbest\u201d chequing account in Canada for everyone. The right choice for one person may not be a good fit for someone else, as it depends on one\u2019s individual needs and lifestyle. That said, it\u2019s no surprise that BMO \u2019s most popular option is the Performance Chequing Account , as it offers a strong balance of features and value for everyday banking.\nBMO\nHow can I save on chequing account fees? You can save on chequing account fees by choosing an account that has no or low monthly fees. For example, the Practical Chequing Account is a low-fee option that offers everyday banking services such as depositing paycheques, paying bills and expenses, and making $0 withdrawals at BMO ATM s. Many chequing accounts also waive monthly fees if you maintain a minimum balance, or offer discounts for groups like students and seniors.",
          "anchor_type": "section",
          "anchor_value": "what-is-the-best-chequing-account-in-canada",
          "page_no": null,
          "chunk_index": 20,
          "field_metadata": {
            "retrieval_mode": "metadata-only",
            "matched_keywords": [
              "banking"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "field_name": "newcomer_plan_flag",
          "candidate_value": true,
          "value_type": "boolean",
          "confidence": 0.59,
          "extraction_method": "heuristic_flag",
          "source_document_id": "src-bmo-html-49c8d8984f930b1c",
          "source_snapshot_id": "snap-7feab1d60acd1387",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-5681ef466f618098",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Are you a student, senior, or newcomer to Canada?\nSome chequing accounts reduce fees (or even remove them altogether) for certain demographics. They also might offer special rewards or bonus features to make banking more accessible and affordable. BMO's NewStart Program , for instance, supports newcomers to Canada by waiving monthly chequing account fees for two years.\nWhen choosing a chequing account, consider how often you bank, the level of branch access you need, the perks you\u2019re interested in, and if you qualify for any specialized plans.",
          "anchor_type": "section",
          "anchor_value": "are-you-a-student-senior-or-newcomer-to-canada",
          "page_no": null,
          "chunk_index": 15,
