          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Do saving accounts have fees?\nNext, let\u2019s examine the fees. While some banks may charge a monthly fee to maintain a savings account, the account may also have a monthly transaction limit, as well as fees for withdrawals or transfers beyond the limit set by the bank. At BMO , there are no monthly fees for any of our savings accounts.\nNext, let\u2019s examine the fees. While some banks may charge a monthly fee to maintain a savings account, the account may also have a monthly transaction limit, as well as fees for withdrawals or transfers beyond the limit set by the bank. At\nBMO\n, there are no monthly fees for any of our savings accounts.\nIt all comes down to the requirements for the savings account you open. Be sure to ask your bank representative questions and do some research to understand all the fees, features and benefits of the account before you open it. Plus, as with any bank account,",
