          "evidence_text_excerpt": "e compared with your traditional savings account. That means your money can grow faster in a HISA than in a traditional savings account. The interest for a HISA is calculated daily on your account balance, but it is paid out monthly, and interest rates are typically quoted on an annual basis.\nNow, when it comes to transactions, you\u2019ll find that most of the typical transaction options offered by a traditional savings account are also offered by a HISA. As far as fees go, HISAs are similar to other traditional savings accounts in that their associated fees can vary, depending on the specific type of account and the financial institution offering it. Some accounts may have monthly fees or fees for certain types or amounts of transactions. At BMO , for example, the high-interest Savings Amplifier Account features no monthly fees, no minimum balance requirement and unlimited free self-serve",
