          "evidence_text_excerpt": "How a high-interest savings account (HISA) works\nLet's dive into the mechanics of a high-interest savings account together.\nA high-interest savings account (HISA) is a bit like a traditional savings account in how it works. You deposit your money and watch it accrue interest, although at a more favourable interest rate compared with your traditional savings account. That means your money can grow faster in a HISA than in a traditional savings account. The interest for a HISA is calculated daily on your account balance, but it is paid out monthly, and interest rates are typically quoted on an annual basis.\nA high-interest savings account (HISA) is a bit like a\nin how it works. You deposit your money and watch it accrue interest, although at a more favourable interest rate compared with your traditional savings account. That means your money can grow faster in a HISA than in a traditional",
