          "evidence_text_excerpt": "utomatically be dispersed into your goal and the Reserve Fund, based on the contribution amounts you\u2019ve set up for each goal and for the Reserve Fund. You can set a contribution ratio for your goals, ranging from 0% to 100%. To transfer funds from one goal to another, go to Goals settings > Move savings around. If you would like to adjust your contributions to your goals, go to Goals Settings > Adjust contribution . What is the Reserve Fund, and how does it work? The Reserve Fund is a portion of your savings account that can be used to contribute to your savings goals. The Reserve Fund makes it easier for you to use a portion of your savings towards your savings goals. You can set a contribution ratio for the Reserve Fund, ranging from 0% to 100%. The Reserve Fund account can\u2019t be deleted, even if you set it to 0%, because it\u2019s required to access the Savings Goals feature. To move funds",
