          "evidence_text_excerpt": "What is the 50/30/20 budget rule?\nThe 50/30/20 budget rule is a guideline for what percentage of your take-home pay should be allocated toward certain categories. This rule is a great way to keep a habit of growing your emergency savings. The 50/30/20 budget rule suggests paying no more than 50% for your needs, 30% for wants, and 20% for savings. In the savings categories, debt repayment is included. If you're just getting started with budgeting and saving, here are six golden rules of saving .",
